Document: AimModifier3D
Path: godot/classes/class_aimmodifier3d.rst
Summary: AimModifier3D is a 3D node that modifies the aim direction of a character based on input and movement.

AimModifier3D inherits from Node3D. This class is part of the Godot engine's 3D character control system, designed to handle aiming mechanics by calculating target directions based on character movement and input axes. Key Rule: Must be used with a CharacterBody3D node to function properly. Warning: Does not work correctly when attached to nodes other than CharacterBody3D. The class provides properties to configure sensitivity, smoothing, and priority for aiming calculations, with default values set to balanced gameplay settings.
