Document: AimModifier3D  
Path: godot/classes/class_aimmodifier3d.rst  
Summary: Methods for configuring bone axes, rotation settings, and relative transformations in AimModifier3D.  

Method: get_forward_axis(index: int) → BoneAxis. Returns the forward axis of the bone.  
Method: get_primary_rotation_axis(index: int) → Axis. Returns the axis of the first rotation. Enabled only if is_using_euler(index) is true.  
Method: is_relative(index: int) → bool. Returns true if the relative option is enabled at the specified index.  
Method: is_using_euler(index: int) → bool. Returns true if rotation uses Euler angles.  
Method: is_using_secondary_rotation(index: int) → bool. Returns true if rotation uses two axes. Enabled only if is_using_euler(index) is true.  
Method: set_forward_axis(index: int, axis: BoneAxis). Sets the forward axis of the bone.  
Method: set_primary_rotation_axis(index: int, axis: Axis). Sets the first rotation axis. Enabled only if is_using_euler(index) is true.  
Method: set_relative(index: int, enabled: bool). Enables or disables relative rotation at the specified index. When true, rotation is applied relative to the pose; when false, it replaces the current pose with the modifier's result.  
Method: set_use_euler(index: int, enabled: bool). Enables or disables Euler-based rotation. When true, uses Euler angles; when false, uses rotation from the forward axis vector and reference vector.  
Method: set_use_secondary_rotation(index: int, enabled: bool). Enables or disables secondary rotation (two axes). Only available if is_using_euler(index) is true.